Hi Cissy and team,


Quick update on our Chinese Medicine Avatar project and where we're heading=
.

Current Status

Good news - we have HeyGen working for avatar streaming. However, given the=
 costs, we're planning to develop our own in-house solution longer term.

Two-Path Approach

Option 1: HeyGen Testing (Available Now)


  *   We can use HeyGen for immediate testing and demos

  *   Good for validating concepts while we build our own tech


Option 2: In-House Development (Medium Term)


  *   Custom solution that's cost-effective and tailored to our needs

  *   Will be ready once we nail down the pedagogical approach

Immediate Focus: Text-Based Testing

Let's prioritize testing scenarios and prompts before adding avatar complex=
ity. We have two platforms ready:


Clinical Handover Testing:


  *   Updated URL: https://lessons.hkbu.tech/api/AccessLessons/ChineseMedTu=
torWebsite

  *   Ready for student testing


New Prototype Platform:


  *   textbot.hkbu.tech - we can set up prototypes here

  *   Perfect for testing different prompts and scenarios

Next Steps

For Cissy & Ellie & John (Pedagogical Focus):


  *   Design lesson plans for interactive tutoring scenarios

  *   Test different clinical handover situations

  *   Define what makes a good TCM conversation


For Andy (Part-time Student Helper) & Kaitai (Full-time Developer):


  *   Set up prototypes on textbot.hkbu.tech

  *   Test various prompts and responses

  *   Support pedagogical team with technical implementation

The Plan Moving Forward

  1.  Focus on scenarios first - get the educational content right

  2.  Test extensively with text-based interactions

  3.  Design lesson plans that actually work for students

  4.  Build tech solution once we know exactly what we need


The streaming avatar tech will be ready when our pedagogical solution is so=
lid. Better to get the teaching approach right first, then add the bells an=
d whistles.


Thoughts? Happy to discuss this week.


Simon


